"{\"uid\": \"si.com-olympics-how-to-watch-shacarri-richardson-2024-paris-olympics\", \"text\": \"American fans are excited to see many of the Team USA athletes compete at the 2024 Paris Olympics, one star being track and field phenom Sha'Carri Richardson.  The sprinter will make her Olympic debut in Paris after her campaign to make the Tokyo Olympics was cut when she tested positive for THC when she took an anti-doping violation.  Richardson enters the Paris Olympicshaving just set a record time of 10.71 secondsin the 100-meter qualifier at the Olympic Trials in June. She will be competing in the 100-meter race in Paris.  If you want to tune in to Richardson's competitions, here's her race schedule.  Date  Time  TV Channel  Competition  Friday, August 2  4:35 a.m. ET  USA Network, E!, Peacock  Women's 100-meter\\u00c2\\u00a0Preliminary Round  Friday, August 2  4:50 a.m. ET  USA Network, E!, Peacock  Women's 100m First Round  Saturday, August 3  2 p.m. ET  USA Network, E!, Peacock  Women's 100m Semifinal  Saturday, August 3  2:20 p.m. ET  USA Network, E!, Peacock  Women's 100m Final  Richardson's Olympic campaign began Aug. 2 with the women's 100-meter preliminary round and first round. She was dominant in her first showing with a 10.94, advancing to the semifinal on Saturday.  Welcome to the Olympic Games, Sha\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099Carri Richardson!#ParisOlympics\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0093\\u00ba E! and Peacockpic.twitter.com/qxtT9xLALw  Impressively, her dominancedidn't even crack her personal top-10 for the event.  The track and field events happening overnight in American time zones will be shown in NBC's primetime show starting at 8 p.m. ET on those nights. The live event can be watched on USA Network and E!, and fans can also stream the races on Peacock.  Loading recommendations... Please wait while we load personalized content recommendations  Madison Williams is a staff writer on the Breaking and Trending News team at Sports Illustrated, where she specializes in tennis but covers a wide range of sports from a national perspective. Before joining SI in 2022, Williams worked at The Sporting News. Having graduated from Augustana College, she completed a master\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s in sports media at Northwestern University.  \\u00c2\\u00a9 2026ABG-SI LLC-SPORTS ILLUSTRATED IS A REGISTERED TRADEMARK OF ABG-SI LLC. - All Rights Reserved. The content on this site is for entertainment and educational purposes only. Betting and gambling content is intended for individuals 21+ and is based on individual commentators' opinions and not that of Sports Illustrated or its affiliates, licensees and related brands. All picks and predictions are suggestions only and not a guarantee of success or profit. If you or someone you know has a gambling problem, crisis counseling and referral services can be accessed by calling 1-800-GAMBLER.\"}"